@node "wotsit" "What is it?"

  @{b}@{fg shine}Info@{fg text}Delve@{ub}

  This is just a program which lets you choose an icon to
  view by selecting it with a file requester.

  When you've chosen an icon, it brings up the Workbench
  Icon Information requester (or SwazInfo/whatever if you
  have one of these installed).

  Now you can easily edit tooltypes that are buried deep
  down in your hard-drive!
@endnode

@node "usage" "Usage"

  @{b}Usage@{ub}

  Just run the program, either from Workbench or the CLI
  (Recommended : stick it in your ToolsDaemon/ToolManager
  setup!).

  Select an icon from the file requester,and then edit the
  icon's tooltypes as normal.

  Note that the requester by default only shows ".info"
  files (ie icons), but you can view programs without icons
  by deleting the #?.info from the pattern section of the
  requester.

  That's it.
@endnode

